
Läslig demo

  [INFO] Readable by default
    Structured output should look intentional without forcing a framework.
    Use laslig for results and diagnostics.
    Keep logging and CLI orchestration separate.


Structured Blocks

  Project
    module: github.com/evanmschultz/laslig
    runtime deps: Charm + stdlib
    task runner: Mage

  Policy
    format  plain
    styled  false

  Surfaces
  - Structured blocks [READY]
    use: records, tables, notices, panels
  - Rich text [READY]
    use: paragraphs, markdown, code, transcripts
  - testjson [LIVE]
    use: Charm-native go test output

  Formats
  format | goal
  -------+--------------------------
  human  | pleasant terminal output
  plain  | stable no-ANSI text
  json   | machine-readable payloads
  One policy, three surfaces.


Rich Text

  Why prose matters
  
  Long-form command output should stay readable without forcing every caller to hand-build wrapped Lip Gloss layouts.
  
  Use Paragraph when a Notice or Panel would be too heavy.

  [SUCCESS] Build ready (mage check)

  # Release Notes
  
  ## Highlights
  
  - one renderer
  - three output surfaces
  - caller-owned logging

  example.go
  
  fmt.Println("hello from laslig")
  
  Rendered through Glamour in styled human mode.

  stderr excerpt
  
  INFO boot complete
  WARN retry scheduled
  ERROR dependency missing

  Why this shape
  
  Fang should own help and command errors. Laslig should own ordinary output blocks, rich text, and stream summaries.
  
  Next up: theme presets and richer test classification.
